# Local dev container (docker run/compose). For a Bzync Cloud deploy, the
# platform DOES seed these as the project's real env vars on first deploy
# (see BZYNC_CLOUD).
#
# phpMyAdmin holds no credentials of its own — PMA_HOST only pre-fills the
# login form's server field, it doesn't log you in. You still enter a real
# MySQL/MariaDB username and password on every visit.

# ── Point at a database (recommended) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Deploy `database/mysql` or `database/mariadb` from this catalog as its
# own app, then set this from its host value (no dashboard linking on this
# tier). Leaves the login form's server field pre-filled and read-only.
# PMA_HOST=<MYSQL_HOST>
# PMA_PORT=<MYSQL_PORT>

# ── Or: allow typing any host at login ─────────────────────────────────────
# Default. Shows a free-text server field so you can connect to any
# MySQL/MariaDB reachable from the container, not just one fixed host. Set
# to 0 once PMA_HOST above is set, to lock the instance to that one server.
PMA_ARBITRARY=1

# ── Misc (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# UPLOAD_LIMIT=64M
# PMA_ABSOLUTE_URI=https://your-domain.example.com/
